// @test regression/INV036-undefined-function-reference
// @description CE10271: an identifier callee must be a built-in or a UDF/method declared earlier in source - undefined names, call-before-definition, and variables-as-callees all error; variables/tuples shadowing a UDF name do NOT break calls to it. Probed 2026-06-05, see INV036.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects errors: 3
// @expects error: line=3, message=/Could not find function or function reference .nonExistentFunction./
// @expects error: line=4, message=/Could not find function or function reference .early./
// @expects error: line=8, message=/Could not find function or function reference .v./

//@version=6
indicator("INV036")
x = nonExistentFunction(close, 14)
y = early(1)
early(n) =>
    n * 2
v = 1
w = v(2)
loss(a) =>
    a + 1
loss = loss(2)
sto() =>
    [close, open]
[sto, sto2] = sto()
scaled(s) =>
    float scaled = ta.sma(s, 2)
    scaled * 2
plot(x + y + w + loss + sto + sto2 + scaled(close))
